# ğŸ¨ CS2DecalBuilder

A GUI-based Python tool for converting and preparing custom image decals for use in **Cities: Skylines II** mods. Easily convert your PNG/JPG files into properly structured decal assets with adjusted metadata and folder structure.

---

## âœ¨ Features

- âœ… Simple **Tkinter GUI** with text input + file/folder browser support  
- âœ… Converts JPG/JPEG to PNG (with proper transparency and resizing)  
- âœ… Adjusts mesh size values in a template JSON based on image dimensions  
- âœ… Renames and structures output folders/files automatically  
- âœ… Places image and decal.json in unique folders (e.g., `tree456/_BaseColorMap.png`)  
- âœ… Fully compatible with **CS2 modding requirements** (via ExtraAssetImporter)

---

## ğŸ–¥ï¸ Requirements

- Python 3.8+
- [Pillow](https://pypi.org/project/Pillow/)  
  ```bash
  pip install pillow
  ```

---

## ğŸš€ Getting Started

1. Clone or download the repo  
2. Install dependencies (`pip install pillow`)  
3. Run the tool  
   ```bash
   python CS2DecalBuilder.py
   ```

---

## ğŸ§° How To Use

1. Launch the tool  
2. Select:
   - ğŸ“ Source folder (image files)
   - ğŸ“ Destination folder (structured output)
   - ğŸ“„ Template JSON file (base decal format)
   - âœï¸ Prefix (used for folder naming like `tree456`)
3. Click **Start Processing**

---

## ğŸ§© Compatibility with Cities: Skylines II

This tool is designed to generate decal folders compatible with the **[ExtraAssetImporter](https://github.com/AlphaGaming7780/ExtraAssetsImporter)** mod.

### âœ… Required for in-game usage:
- [Download on GitHub](https://github.com/AlphaGaming7780/ExtraAssetsImporter)
- [Or from Paradox Mods](https://mods.paradoxplaza.com/mods/80529/Windows)

### ğŸ“ Install Decals Here:
```bash
C:\Users\USERNAME\AppData\LocalLow\Colossal Order\Cities Skylines II\ModsData\ExtraAssetsImporter\CustomDecals\CategoryName
```

Replace `USERNAME` with your Windows username.  
Make sure to use an appropriate **CategoryName** (see [EAI Wiki â€“ Category Names](https://github.com/AlphaGaming7780/ExtraAssetsImporter/wiki/Custom-Decals)).

