## ğŸ“ Mesh Size Calculation

Automatically determines mesh values from the texture resolution using rules like:

| Resolution       | Mesh Size Output      |
|------------------|------------------------|
| 512 x 512        | `"x": 4, "z": 4`       |
| 1024 x 1536      | `"x": 6, "z": 9`       |
| 2048 x 512       | `"x": 16, "z": 4`      |

---

## âš ï¸ Limitations

This script was built and tested for creating **WallDecor** assets.  
It may work with other decal categories, but:

> âŒ It does **not** generate `_MaskMap.png` or `_NormalMap.png` files.  
> âœ… It only creates a `_BaseColorMap.png`.

For best results, use categories that **do not** require those extra maps.

---

## â— Troubleshooting

- **Unity errors?** Small or oddly sized images are padded/resized to avoid texture initialization failures
- **Black images in game?** Ensure you're not using formats or dimensions that Unity can't interpret â€” stick to common resolutions like 512x512, 1024x1024, 1024x1536, etc.
- **See also:** [EAI Wiki â€“ Custom Decals](https://github.com/AlphaGaming7780/ExtraAssetsImporter/wiki/Custom-Decals)

